---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";

const title = "Privacy Policy — Odal Node";
const description =
  "How the Odal Node website handles your data: no cookies, no analytics, no third-party trackers. Hosted on Cloudflare Pages with zero data collection.";

// This policy covers the website at odal-node.io only — a static site with no
// backend. How the Odal Node software handles product data is a separate,
// architectural question; see /trust.
const MAILBOX = "security@odal-node.io";

// TODO(legal): once a registered entity exists, name the data controller and
// its jurisdiction here and in the "Who is responsible" section below.
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <!-- <Section eyebrow="Privacy" title="What this site collects, and what it does not.">
    <p>
      This policy covers the website at <strong>odal-node.io</strong> — the pages
      you are reading now. It is deliberately short, because the site is
      deliberately simple: it is a static website with no backend, no accounts,
      and no database. There is nothing here that quietly watches you.
    </p>
    <p>
      How the Odal Node <em>software</em> handles product data is a separate
      question, and an architectural one rather than a policy one — the node
      validates and signs locally, then discards the raw input. That story is
      told on the <a href="/trust">trust page</a>. This page is only about the
      website.
    </p>
  </Section> -->

  <Section eyebrow="Privacy Policy" title="No cookies, no analytics, no trackers.">
    <ul>
      <li>The site sets <strong>no cookies</strong> and uses no local storage to track you.</li>
      <li>There is <strong>no analytics</strong> — no Google Analytics, Plausible, Fathom, or any equivalent.</li>
      <li>There are <strong>no third-party trackers, advertising pixels, or social embeds</strong>.</li>
      <li>We do not build a profile of you, and we do not sell or share data — there is nothing to sell.</li>
      <li>The only data that exists is what your browser unavoidably sends to load a web page, and anything you choose to email us.</li>
    </ul>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Hosting" title="What the host sees. " tone="tinted">
    <p>
      The site is served as static files by <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong>.
      As with any website, your browser must connect to a server to load a page,
      and that connection is visible to the host. To deliver the site and protect
      it from abuse, Cloudflare processes standard request metadata: your
      <strong>IP address</strong>, the time of the request, the page requested,
      your browser's user-agent string, and similar technical details.
    </p>
    <p>
      We use this for nothing. We do not run analytics over it and we do not
      receive it as an identifiable record of you. It is processed by Cloudflare
      as our hosting provider — acting as a data processor on our behalf — for
      content delivery, TLS, and security (such as DDoS protection), under
      Cloudflare's own terms. See
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener">Cloudflare's privacy policy</a>.
      Our legal basis for this processing is our legitimate interest in serving
      and securing the site.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Off-site links" title="Where the site sends you.">
    <p>
      Some links lead off this site — the <a href="https://docs.odal-node.io" rel="noopener">documentation</a>,
      our <a href="https://github.com/odal-node" rel="noopener">GitHub organisation</a>,
      and a few cited standards. Once you follow them you are on someone else's
      property, governed by their privacy practices, not this one. We have no
      control over what those services collect.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Your rights" title="What you can ask of us." tone="tinted">
    <p>
      Under the GDPR and equivalent laws you can ask us to confirm what personal
      data we hold about you, to correct it, to send you a copy, or to delete it.
      Because the only personal data we hold is whatever you have emailed us, a
      request usually amounts to "delete our correspondence", which we will do.
    </p>
    <p>
      To exercise any of these rights, or to ask a privacy question, write to
      <a href={`mailto:${MAILBOX}`}>{MAILBOX}</a>. If you believe we have handled
      your data improperly, you also have the right to lodge a complaint with your
      local data protection authority.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Responsibility & changes" title="Who is responsible, and how this page changes.">
    <p>
      <strong>Odal Node</strong> is responsible for this website and for the
      personal data described above. For any data or privacy matter, the contact
      is <a href={`mailto:${MAILBOX}`}>{MAILBOX}</a>.
    </p>
</Base>
